      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If someone wears traditional clothing, they are often seen as being culturally rooted rather than \"unprofessional,\" but they might be perceived as less globally adaptable depending on the audience. Different communication styles, especially those that are more expressive, can be misinterpreted by those from very reserved cultures as being too aggressive or lacking polish. Ultimately, the perception is often filtered through the lens of the dominant culture present in those high-level circles.",
